flowRoot.flowPara: Users shouldn't have to leave the Overview to be able read information about running apps or to click a button in a confirmation dialog.
This is your average GNOME desktop in Overview Mode. Let's close that text editor!
Yes, this dialog appears on the overview and you can interract with it without leaving the overview!
But that's not all, you can Play/Pause your favorite music player; check on the progress of your downloading torrents ;) and more!
Of course everything, like the close button, only appears on hover to reduce the noise.
